From: James Smart <jsmart2021@gmail.com>
Date: Fri, 3 Jun 2022 10:43:24 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] scsi: lpfc: Address NULL pointer dereference after
 starget_to_rport()
References: bsc#1012628
Patch-mainline: 5.18.4
Git-commit: 6f808bd78e8296b4ded813b7182988d57e1f6176

commit 6f808bd78e8296b4ded813b7182988d57e1f6176 upstream.

Calls to starget_to_rport() may return NULL.  Add check for NULL rport
before dereference.

Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20220603174329.63777-5-jsmart2021@gmail.com
Fixes: bb21fc9911ee ("scsi: lpfc: Use fc_block_rport()")
Cc: <stable@vger.kernel.org> # v5.18
Co-developed-by: Justin Tee <justin.tee@broadcom.com>
Signed-off-by: Justin Tee <justin.tee@broadcom.com>
Signed-off-by: James Smart <jsmart2021@gmail.com>
Signed-off-by: Martin K. Petersen <martin.petersen@oracle.com>
Signed-off-by: Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@linuxfoundation.org>
Signed-off-by: Jiri Slaby <jslaby@suse.cz>
---
 drivers/scsi/lpfc/lpfc_scsi.c | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/scsi/lpfc/lpfc_scsi.c b/drivers/scsi/lpfc/lpfc_scsi.c
index f617a2ef6b0f..add238dc599b 100644
--- a/drivers/scsi/lpfc/lpfc_scsi.c
+++ b/drivers/scsi/lpfc/lpfc_scsi.c
@@ -6316,6 +6316,9 @@ lpfc_device_reset_handler(struct scsi_cmnd *cmnd)
 	int status;
 	u32 logit = LOG_FCP;
 
+	if (!rport)
+		return FAILED;
+
 	rdata = rport->dd_data;
 	if (!rdata || !rdata->pnode) {
 		lpfc_printf_vlog(vport, KERN_ERR, LOG_TRACE_EVENT,
@@ -6394,6 +6397,9 @@ lpfc_target_reset_handler(struct scsi_cmnd *cmnd)
 	unsigned long flags;
 	DECLARE_WAIT_QUEUE_HEAD_ONSTACK(waitq);
 
